  <h1 class="margin-bottom large-title">Get involved</h1>

  <div class="margin-bottom">
    <h2 class="bold">I'm a Java / OpenJDK User</h2>
    <p>
      We provide rock-solid binaries to the highest quality possible utilising existing OpenJDK test suites
      (via <em>jtreg</em> tests, <em>jcov</em> test coverage et al) and over 60,000 other OSS donated test suites.
      See <a href="./support.html">Support</a> for community and commercial support options.
    </p>

    <h3 class="bold">Available Platforms</h3>
    <p>
      We currently support ARM 32/64 (aarch 32/64), Linux x64, Windows, Solaris (Intel), MacOS and several other
      Linux variants including PPC and AIX.
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="margin-bottom">
    <h2 class="bold">I'm an OpenJDK and/or an Eclipse OpenJ9 Developer</h2>
    <p>
      We provide <a target="_blank" href="https://www.github.com/AdoptOpenJDK">infrastructure as code</a>,
      and a <a href="https://ci.adoptopenjdk.net">Build and test farm</a> for OpenJDK and Eclipse OpenJ9 developers.
      A future version of this build farm will act as a patch submission mechanism for OpenJDK and Eclipse OpenJ9 developers to submit,
      review and test patches for multiple platforms <strong>before</strong> submitting to their respective upstream project.
    </p>

    <h3 class="bold">Source Forests</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>OpenJDK:</strong> We have clones starting from OpenJDK 8 (jdk8u) all the way through to the latest development version.
      We also cover some projects that have yet to be merged with mainline, e.g. Projects Amber, Valhalla and more.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Eclipse OpenJ9:</strong> We pull directly from <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/eclipse/openj9">Eclipse OpenJ9's GitHub repository</a>. OpenJDK class libraries are
      included as part of the build process.
    </p>
  </div>

